//(SCP-3085 gasps. Anomalous activity stops.)//

**Dr. Erikson:** That’s it. It’s OK. It’s OK.

**SCP-3085:** //(Inaudible)//

**Dr. Erikson:** What was that?

**SCP-3085:** //(Faintly)// It… hurts. It hurts so much.

**Dr. Erikson:** I ca-

//(SCP-3085 starts violently coughing)//

**Dr. Erikson:** Do you need medical attention?

**SCP-3085:** No!

//(The lightbulbs of the containment cell shatter. )//

**SCP-3085:** No… No doctors.

//(Pause)//

**Dr. Erikson:** What can I do for you today, SCP-3085?

**SCP-3085:** You have to- You have to kill me.

**Dr. Erikson:** (Pauses) I… I can’t do that, SCP-3085.

**SCP-3085:** Please Bill, I- You… I can’t live like this.

**Dr. Erikson:** SCP-3085… You’re agitated. Why don’t you calm down and then we can-

**SCP-3085:** No. I have to do this now. I’ve been lucky, most of my kind don’t live this long but…
I have. I’m aging, all of me. I can feel it, I can feel myself losing my mind. Do you have any idea what that feels like? To watch yourself go insane?

**Dr. Erikson:** N-no, I-

**SCP-3085:** It’s the scariest thing in the fucking world. I’m losing myself, Bill, and I'm losing control. My powers have always been a curse and- (Pause)

**Dr. Erikson:** SCP-3085?

**SCP-3085:** I’m terrified of what happens when I lose control. Bill, I need you to understand. These moments of lucidity aren’t an alleviation, they’re just more pain. You’ve seen it. I’m losing control of my powers. My existence is pain and it needs to end. Please, Doctor. I’m begging you. If you don’t, I’ll fucking do it myself.

**Dr. Erikson:** Raul, I’m… I’m sorry.

